# VoltPro ‚Äî Project Context

## What is VoltPro?
B2B platform for Electrical Engineers targeting Fortune 500 companies.
Covers electrical infrastructure setup, project management, and workforce coordination.

## Core Feature Modules (build in order, part by part)
1. **Engineer Directory** ‚Äî Browse available engineers, filter by specialisation
2. **Booking** ‚Äî Book engineers for projects
3. **Lead Management** ‚Äî Import leads, assign to users
4. **Quotes** ‚Äî Convert qualified leads to quotes / estimates
5. **Jobs** ‚Äî Accept or decline (with reason), plan and schedule
6. **Projects** ‚Äî Track progress and profitability

## Design System
- Theme: **Midnight + Volt Green** ‚Äî Background `#0A0F1E`, Accent `#22C55E`
- Font: Outfit (loaded via Google Fonts in `index.css`)
- **Styling: Tailwind CSS v4** ‚Äî use utility classes in JSX; no separate CSS files for component styles
- Custom design tokens are defined in `@theme` in `index.css` and map directly to Tailwind utilities:
  | Token | Tailwind class |
  |---|---|
  | `#0A0F1E` | `bg-volt-black` / `text-volt-black` |
  | `#0F1628` | `bg-volt-secondary` |
  | `#22C55E` | `bg-volt-accent` / `text-volt-accent` |
  | `#16A34A` | `bg-volt-accent-hover` |
  | `#1E2D4A` | `border-volt-border` |
  | `#F8FAFC` | `text-volt-text` |
  | `#94A3B8` | `text-volt-muted` |
- Only write CSS in `index.css` for values that **cannot** be expressed as Tailwind utilities (e.g. multi-layer `background` gradients with image positioning)
- Use arbitrary values `[value]` for one-off sizes, shadows, or tracking not in the theme scale
- Mobile-first: use Tailwind responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) ‚Äî never separate media query blocks in components
- Glow effects: `drop-shadow-[0_0_Xpx_rgba(...)]` or `shadow-[0_0_Xpx_rgba(...)]`
- No inline styles for static values; use Tailwind classes

## Build Approach
- **Build part by part** ‚Äî never scaffold entire modules at once
- One component at a time, confirm before moving to the next

# React Standards

## Components
- Use functional components only ‚Äî no class components
- One component per file; filename matches the component name
- Keep components under 300 lines; split into smaller ones if larger

## Naming
- Components: `PascalCase` (e.g., `VoltStoreCard`)
- Hooks: `camelCase` prefixed with `use` (e.g., `useVoltStores`)
- Event handlers: prefix with `handle` (e.g., `handleSubmit`)

## Hooks
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks in `src/hooks/`
- Never call hooks inside conditions or loops

## State & Data Fetching
- Use `useState` / `useReducer` for local state
- Use custom hooks to encapsulate API calls ‚Äî keep components free of fetch logic

## Styling
- **Always use Tailwind utility classes** ‚Äî write classes directly in JSX
- Only add to `index.css` when Tailwind utilities are insufficient (complex multi-layer backgrounds, keyframe animations)
- Avoid inline styles except for truly dynamic runtime values (e.g. `style={{ width: progress + '%' }}`)

## Error Handling

```jsx
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî silent failure
const data = await fetch('/api/stores').then(r => r.json());

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî handle errors explicitly
const res = await fetch('/api/stores');
if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Failed to fetch stores: ${res.status}`);
const data = await res.json();
```

## Imports
- Keep third-party imports before local imports
- No unused imports

## README Updates
- When asked to "update README", add short bullet-point notes only
- No lengthy explanations ‚Äî just enough to jog memory when returning to the project
- Use tables and code snippets over paragraphs
- Group by topic; keep each section under 10 lines
